A frontline gubernatorial aspirant in Kaduna State under the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Mohammed Sani Abbas, has announced the appointment of his Campaign Chairman, Directors and Coordinators ahead of the party primaries. A statement by the Director Public Affairs and Corporate Communications, Victor Mathew Bobai, announcing the development after a successful consultation, said Abbas approved the appointment of Chief A. G. Haruna as the Chairman, Campaign Council of the Barrister Mohammed Sani Abbas Campaign Organisation. Chief Haruna is a former State Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party. He also approved the appointment of Alhaji Bala Alwa’u as Deputy Chairman of the Campaign Council.   Inside story of Uba Sani’s emergence as Kaduna APC…     Abdulrazaq deserves another term – Kwara monarchs     2023: Money, godfatherism will play little or no role in…   Others are Director Contact and Mobilisation, Adamu Abdullahi, aka Charles Tailor, Director Media, Ishak Alhassan Kauran-Mata and Deputy Director Media, Mr Amos Tauna. Mr. Victor Mathew Bobai is appointed Director of Public Affairs and Corporate Communications, while Abubakar Yusuf Jamwala is appointed the Deputy Director Public Affairs and Corporate Communications. Also appointed are Director of Finance, Alhaji Abubakar Sadiq Mohammed; Director Legal Services Aminu Abdulrashid; Director Compliance Yusuf Sambo; Director Research and Strategy Dr. Umar Tabari and Deputy Director Research and Strategy, Wali Mukhtar. Zonal Coordinators are Alhaji Isiaku Pengo (Zone1), Alhaji Abubakar Umar Sallau (Zone 2) and Hon Kumai Badu (Zone 3). The appointments are with immediate effects.